Bentley: Android certificate-hash compatibility.

On Android we must use the legacy X509_NAME_hash_old() so that V2 checkpoints can be
downloaded (see iModelCore/libsrc/openssl/READ_BEFORE_UPDATING_CODE.md). Guarded by
__ANDROID__ so all other platforms keep the default behavior.

X509_NAME_hash_old() does not set the `i` out-parameter that X509_NAME_hash_ex() sets,
so we must initialize `i = 1` ("assume ok") before the `if (i == 0) goto finish;` check
below. Omitting this leaves `i` uninitialized and intermittently crashes during TLS
certificate verification (regression previously fixed in imodel-native PR #986).

--- a/crypto/x509/by_dir.c
+++ b/crypto/x509/by_dir.c
@@ -257,7 +257,12 @@ static int get_cert_by_subject_ex(X509_LOOKUP *xl, X509_LOOKUP_TYPE type,
     }
 
     ctx = (BY_DIR *)xl->method_data;
-    h = X509_NAME_hash_ex(name, libctx, propq, &i);
+#if defined(__ANDROID__)
+    h = X509_NAME_hash_old(name);
+    i = 1; /* X509_NAME_hash_old() does not set i; assume ok (see imodel-native PR #986) */
+#else
+    h = X509_NAME_hash_ex(name, libctx, propq, &i);
+#endif
     if (i == 0)
         goto finish;
     for (i = 0; i < sk_BY_DIR_ENTRY_num(ctx->dirs); i++) {
